document_data.History:
When Sauk was fifteen, he killed his father's son. He joined the [[Blades of the Old Man]] at some point between then and {{yearlink|1365}}, when he was a part of the raid on the [[Yuirwood]] where Kheil was captured; he considered that the blackest of his life.{{cite book/Sentinelspire||7}} 

After Talieth discovered [[Kheil]] was alive, Sauk had sent Taaki to lure him out of the steppes, looking for his aid in slaying the [[Old Man of the Mountain]]. After finding him and learning he went by Berun, he told him that [[Chereth]] was still alive, that the Old Man of the Mountain drained his druidic powers for his own use in between tortures. Though Berun offered to bring a force of servants of [[Silvanus]], Sauk refused to allow that many outsiders to enter the hidden fortress. To get Berun to go with him, he attempted to threaten [[Lewan]], his apprentice. After Berun's escape attempt ended in him being swallowed by a [[shambling mound]], he took [[Lewan]] back to [[Sentinelspire]] anyway, expecting him to maybe be of some use.

During a conversation with Talieth, he realized Berun might not have died.{{cite book/Sentinelspire||20}} Later, when Lewan requested to be allowed to purify himself in the wild, it was Sauk that accompanied him; the half-orc offered the young man the chance to flee, if he so desired.{{cite book/Sentinelspire||22}} He witnessed the exchange between Lewan and the Old Man of the Mountain,{{cite book/Sentinelspire||23}} then questioned the pupil about it, finally relating this to Talieth.{{cite book/Sentinelspire||24}}

On the night of [[Tarsakh 25]], he fought several blades loyal to the Old Man,{{cite book/Sentinelspire||30}} at least one [[killoren]],{{cite book/Sentinelspire||39}} and was instrumental in defeating the Old Man himself.{{cite book/Sentinelspire||40}}
